With the AsAflex, young people are supported in finding a training place and on the way to successfully completing their training - flexibly and completely adapted to individual needs. Trainees and training companies receive continuous socio-educational support from specialists. The trainees receive preparatory offers and assistance tailored to them, while the companies are supported, for example, in organisational issues or in the search for suitable trainees.&nbsp;
Who is AsAflex aimed at?&nbsp;To young people who want to do a dual apprenticeship or are currently preparing for an apprenticeship in an introductory qualification.
Entry can begin in all apprenticeship years. Whenever there is a need for support.
More info here:&nbsp;
Assisted Training (AsA) | Federal Employment Agency (arbeitsagentur.de)
