For many people, the question arises: What happens if I can no longer work in my old age? For this purpose, Germany has the social security system of the German pension insurance (DRV). The website of the German pension insurance offers a lot of information and can answer some questions about pensions
 Deutsche Rentenversicherung
In principle, the pension is paid for by contributions from compulsory insurance jobs. As a rule, halfof the contribution is paid by the employer and half by the employee.&nbsp;
If you are now in a position to claim a pension, you must apply for it. The pension is not paid automatically. You apply for this at least 3 months before you plan to retire. This makes the transition from employment to retirement easier.
You can find the nearest advice centre on pension insurance here. There you can get more detailed information about your model of pension and other benefit.&nbsp;
However, the pension insurance does not only pay a pension, but also provides other benefits. This includes, for example, rehabilitation measures in order to be able to work again. It is important that the later pension benefit does not decrease as a result. It may even increase if such a measure keeps you fit for work for longer.

